            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The measured total current I_total through R3 (with both sources active) was compared against the algebraic sum ΣIk = I₁ + I₂ obtained by superposition for all 10 trial readings. The percentage error between the measured I_total and ΣIk was computed for each trial. The results confirm that the superposition principle holds within acceptable experimental error margins for the linear resistive network."
                }
